assigned_issues.description:
copy/pasting context from discord:

1. Was running into a lot of issues here. After refreshing my bot token and trial/erroring with various permissions combinations, I was eventually having to step through code in PyCord to understand what was going wrong. When a bot is registered with discord, several API calls to register (and set permissions for) the various slash commands are sent to discord. In this case, when I was starting the kevin Malone bot locally, PyCord was registering the commands that KevinMalone uses with the development application/bot account that I set up on discord. I don't know why exactly this started to break, but PyCord was attempting to issue a PUT to the /applications/{application.id}/guilds/{guild.id}/commands/{command.id}/permissions endpoint when attempting to set the permissions of the slash commands. This is after the commands were registered. Note that we don't configure specific permissions for ***any*** of these commands but PyCord is still making this call to the discord API. This call was failing with a 405: Method Not Allowed. After checking in the discord developer documentation ([https://discord.com/developers/docs/interactions/application-commands#permissions](https://discord.com/developers/docs/interactions/application-commands#permissions)), I noticed that a particular kind of token was needed for this operation:

   > Command permissions can only be updated using a Bearer token. Authenticating with a bot token will result in an error.

    I stepped through the PyCord code, and sure enough, only a bot token (which was correctly being passed from my .env) was being passed to the interaction with the discord API. I checked the commit we're using for PyCord (from early January) against latest master (udpated May 1) and saw there were significant changes to the command registration flow. To see if it fixed the issue, I upgraded our import of PyCord to the latest commit, and the issue was fixed. I suspect that this new token requirement for command registration was instituted in the last month, or there's something particular about dev setups that lead to this bad flow being hit.... ~but I'm not sure why I was not hitting this issue before.~ due to the recent breaking change in discord token requirements for updating permissions **(edited)**

   I'm going to issue a PR to bump the Pycord version, since on the next kevin Malone update, the redeployment of the bot will likely fail.
assigned_issues.title: Fix for breaking discord api change

v0 Specs:

1. **/Add DAO command**:
   1. First asks user for the GuildID of the DAO they want
   2. This creates a record in the Guild with the GuildID in guild_ID and with govrn_supported = FALSE
      1. If the guildID already exists in the Guild Table, don't add a new record, just have the user go through the join flow. (Send a message saying "good news! your dao is already onboarded to govrn)
   3. Then have the user go through the /join flow for the new guild (so record shows up in table)
   4. This should now allow the user to see the DAO in the DAO picker

Govrn server potentially be that portal to report for non onboarded dao.

assigned_issues.description:
```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (Initial View)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've clicked on the "Submit" from the "Reptoring Form"
	And I've entered all of the required fields, and they are all validated
	Then I see the Proof Modal where I can submit my proof of contribution
```

```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (Valid Proof of Contribution)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've added my Proof of Contribution into the "Proof Modal"
	And it has passed validation (valid form of Proof)
	Then I see a confirmation that my Proof has been submitted
	And I'm redirected to the Govrn app / "Contribution List"
```

```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (Invalid Proof of Contribution)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've added my Proof of Contribution into the "Proof Modal"
	And it has not passed validation (invalid form of Proof)
	Then I see an alert that my Proof isn't valid, and a list of valid Proofs
	And I'm prompted to add a valid Proof
```

```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (No Proof Added)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've clicked on the "Submit" from the "Reptoring Form"
	And I've not entered any Proof into the Proof Modal input
	Then I see an alert telling me to add a Proof before clicking "Submit"
```
assigned_issues.title: Reporting Form

created_issues.description:
```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (Initial View)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've clicked on the "Submit" from the "Reptoring Form"
	And I've entered all of the required fields, and they are all validated
	Then I see the Proof Modal where I can submit my proof of contribution
```

```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (Valid Proof of Contribution)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've added my Proof of Contribution into the "Proof Modal"
	And it has passed validation (valid form of Proof)
	Then I see a confirmation that my Proof has been submitted
	And I'm redirected to the Govrn app / "Contribution List"
```

```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (Invalid Proof of Contribution)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've added my Proof of Contribution into the "Proof Modal"
	And it has not passed validation (invalid form of Proof)
	Then I see an alert that my Proof isn't valid, and a list of valid Proofs
	And I'm prompted to add a valid Proof
```

```
Feature: Reporting Form - Proof Modal (No Proof Added)
Scenario: User has clicked on the "Submit" button in the "Reporting Form"
	Given that I've clicked on the "Submit" from the "Reptoring Form"
	And I've not entered any Proof into the Proof Modal input
	Then I see an alert telling me to add a Proof before clicking "Submit"
```
created_issues.title: Reporting Form

created_issues.description:
* What needs to be done?
* What are our dependencies?

Ultimately what's needed:

1. Be able to report a contributions to a DAO not yet onboarded to Govrn
2. Be able to report a contributions that aren't associated to any DAO

Implications:

1. Need to allow users to upload a DAO ID for them to report to
2. Need to associate the reporting form with the user instead of the DAO
   1. Make the reported to guild an option on the form
3. Implications on the points command??

Specs for Implication 1:

1. **/Add DAO command**:
   1. First asks user for the GuildID of the DAO they want
   2. This creates a record in the Guild with the GuildID in guild_ID and with govrn_supported = FALSE
      1. If the guildID already exists in the Guild Table, don't add a new record, just have the user go through the join flow. (Send a message saying "good news! your dao is already onboarded to govrn)
   3. Then have the user go through the /join flow for the new guild (so record shows up in table)
   4. This should now allow the user to see the DAO in the DAO picker
created_issues.title: Spec/Brainstorm Moving away from daos in KevinMalone -> Aaron to create HackMD on this

The real requirement:  How do we ensure that fake bots aren't scamming users.

If no way to interact via DMs with DMs being disabled, then lets do ephemeral channels.

**Cool Idea:**  Have all govrn users create a discord channel of just them with their own bot.
